I thought we were emerging out the years of uncertainty. 
Seems either events are "sold out" in a micro-second or no one is interested? Even a major singer like Bryan Adams had to cancel a tour here 😒

The issue with a country music festival is that you need major American country artists performing to attract the most British country fans. Sadly most British Country fans are not interested in British Country artists. Money is not the issue as when I was in Stratford yesterday there were thousands of people heading to West Ham United football ground to see Green Day. There are also big crowds at Glastonbury. I was at Black Deer Festival and there were big crowds there. Morgan Wade did two sold out shows at The Garage a few days ago and Kezia Gill has already sold out two of her tour dates in November so money is not the problem so you have to look at the line up for the festival.

I guess one of the lessons from this is that we need to commit earlier to costly events we'll likely go to. I did commit early to Buckle & Boots & the West Country Music Festival 2022 but must admit that I was hedging bets on a few others, this one included. I'd likely have gone, as I have before, but hadn't booked a ticket yet. Booked for next week's The 7 Hills Fest in the last couple of days. So sorry for all those involved with Tennessee Fields particularly as most of the hard work will already have been put in.
